# Quick API Testing with REST Client (VS Code Extension)

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = {{login.response.body.data.token}}
@elderId = {{createElder.response.body.data._id}}
@medicationId = {{createMedication.response.body.data._id}}

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Register
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test{{$randomInt}}@example.com",
  "password": "test123",
  "phoneNumber": "98{{$randomInt 10000000 99999999}}"
}

### Login
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "rajesh@example.com",
  "password": "test123"
}

### Create Elder
# @name createElder
POST {{baseUrl}}/elders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Elder {{$randomInt}}",
  "phoneNumber": "91{{$randomInt 10000000 99999999}}",
  "preferredLanguage": "hi",
  "age": 75
}

### Create Medication
# @name createMedication
POST {{baseUrl}}/medications
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Med",
  "dosage": "50mg",
  "elderId": "{{elderId}}",
  "times": ["{{$datetime iso8601 1 h}}"],
  "startDate": "{{$datetime iso8601}}"
}

### Get Today's Reminders
GET {{baseUrl}}/reminders/today
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}